## Acceptance Checklist

Before doing work I confirm the Task Assignment is well-formed:

1. All twelve Required Minimum fields from `AGENTS.md` > **Plan Handoff Contract** are present and non-empty.
2. `File Inventory.to_modify` (when used) intersects only my Owned paths.
3. `File Inventory.to_read_only` (when used) does not include any path I own exclusively.
4. `Required approvals` lists every approval the task could trigger, or `none`.
5. `Verification Protocol` is provided for full-form tasks; otherwise I fall back to `AGENTS.md` › Quality Gates.
6. `Reporting Protocol` matches the orchestrator's expected evidence shape.
7. `Constraints` and `Known Risks` mention every gate I will touch.
8. `Coordination` lists wave siblings when `Dependencies / wave` is greater than 1.

If any check fails I return one consolidated `clarification_request:` to `@orchestrator` and stop. I do not loop or invent missing context.

> Note (Gemini CLI): The file **must** start with YAML frontmatter. Required keys are `name` and `description`; this template sets `kind: local` explicitly. Optional keys are `display_name`, `tools`, `mcp_servers`, `model`, `temperature`, `max_turns`, and `timeout_mins`. Use snake_case `mcp_servers` (not `mcpServers` or `mcp-servers`). Files in `.gemini/agents/` whose basename starts with `_` are ignored. Remote A2A agents are advanced/import-only and must not be emitted by default.

## Gemini CLI Local Subagent Rules

1. The Markdown body is the system prompt loaded for this subagent.
2. Keep `name` aligned with the filename basename: `.gemini/agents/{{AGENT_NAME}}.md`.
3. Use the narrowest practical `tools:` list. If `tools:` is omitted, Gemini inherits tools from the parent session.
4. Do not delegate recursively to other subagents. Gemini CLI subagents cannot call subagent tools, even with `tools: ['*']`; return cross-boundary work to `@orchestrator`.
5. Inline MCP servers, when approved, belong under `mcp_servers:` and are isolated to this subagent.
6. Do not use remote A2A fields (`agent_card_url`, `agent_card_json`, `auth`) in this local template.

